# 📚 Chat with PDF — Complete Project Documentation

> A **RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)** application that lets you upload a PDF and ask questions about it using AI. The AI answers *only* from the uploaded document — no hallucinations.

---

## 1. What Is This Project?

This is a **web application** where you can:
1. **Upload a PDF** (research paper, textbook, notes, etc.)
2. **Ask questions** in a chat interface
3. **Get AI-generated answers** based *only* on the content of that PDF

The AI never invents information — if the answer isn't in the PDF, it says so.

---

## 2. Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[🧑 User / Browser] -->|Upload PDF| B[Flask Server - app.py]
    A -->|Ask Question| B
    B -->|Save PDF to uploads/| C[File System]
    B -->|Extract + Chunk + Index| D[RAG Engine - rag_engine.py]
    D -->|Read PDF pages| E[PyPDF2]
    D -->|Split text into chunks| F[LangChain Text Splitter]
    D -->|Generate embeddings| G["HuggingFace all-MiniLM-L6-v2"]
    D -->|Store vectors| H[ChromaDB - chroma_db/]
    D -->|Retrieve relevant chunks| H
    D -->|Generate answer| I["Ollama LLM (llama3.2)"]
    B -->|Return answer| A
```

---

